Car Pool by Laura Hembree
March 14 - April 8
Stages Repertory Theatre is proud to present the Southwest premiere of Laur=
a=20
Hembree's poignant look at the corporate workplace, Car Pool.  Directed by=
=20
Peter Webster, Car Pool previews March 14 and 15, and opens on Friday, Marc=
h=20
16. Performances run Wednesdays through Sundays through April 8.

Five men, one car and a daily commute from the suburbs are the elements tha=
t=20
ignite Car Pool, an incisive examination of how corporate culture impacts t=
he=20
lives of its employees.  The effects of a workplace plagued by down sizing=
=20
layoffs and fear are traced over a six-month period in the conversations of=
=20
these "grandsons of Willy Loman", who must cope with crisis not only in the=
ir=20
careers, but in their personal lives as well  Several of the issues raised =
by=20
the recent spate of corporate and dot-com layoffs are addressed in this=20
well-timed new production.  The New York Times calls Car Pool "a smart,=20
neatly-tailored work."

Call Stages today at 713.527.8243! Tickets also available at the Stages Box=
=20
Office or on-line at www.stagestheatre.com.  Stages is located at 3201 Alle=
n=20
Parkway at Waugh Dr.  Performances are Wed. - Thurs. at 7:30 p.m., Fri. -=
=20
Sat. at 8:00 p.m.,Sun. at 3:00 p.m.




